 for bestpractices and # Admin Controls

## Overview
Build a robust Admin Controls suite for QuestHabit that enables secure admin operations including user moderation, refunds, and special content operations. The system must support RBAC, impersonation mode for support, soft-delete and suspend with audit logs and undo, MFA-secured admin auth with IP allowlisting, and a cohesive Admin Dashboard plus dedicated pages for content moderation and user management. The UI must align with the project’s playful yet calm design system, ensure runtime safety for all data handling (as outlined in the Mandatory Coding Standards), and provide a clear, auditable trail of admin actions.

## Components to Build
- Admin Dashboard (page_admin_dashboard)
  - High-level metrics (KPIs, fraud flags, active users, revenue-related refunds)
  - Quick actions (suspend user, issue refund, export data, impersonate)
  - Search and filters for users and events
  - Real-time/near-real-time data visuals (sparklines, small charts)
- Admin — User Management (page_admin_users)
  - User list with search, filters (status, role, last active), and bulk actions
  - View profile detail drawer/modal (improper access controls enforced)
  - Suspend/Unsuspend, Soft-delete/Restore, Export user data (CSV/JSON)
  - Audit trail access and export
  - Impersonation banner and limits
- Admin — Content Moderation (page_admin_moderation)
  - Manage reported content, moderation decisions, challenges, and leaderboard disputes
  - Review reports, take actions (remove content, warn, suspend posters)
  - Moderation queue, status tracking, and undo/rollback of actions
  - Special content operations (feature content, pin, promote, adjust visibility)
- Admin Roles and Security
  - RBAC definitions (Admin, Moderator, Support, Auditor)
  - Access control checks on both frontend and backend
  - MFA enrollment, IP allowlisting, and session management
- Audit Logging and Undo
  - Centralized audit logs for all admin actions
  - Undo/rollback capability for critical actions (suspend, delete, refund, content removal)
- Impersonation Mode (Support)
  - Impersonation banner, restricted actions, and auditable impersonation sessions
  - Safe exit paths and activity isolation
- Data Export and Compliance
  - Export user data, moderation actions, and audit trails
  - Data retention and privacy safeguards
- API Gateways and Backend Integration
  - Secure endpoints with RBAC, request validation, and rate limiting
  - Soft-delete boolean flags, suspend flags, and audit event records
  - Supabase or alternative DB layer compatibility with safe query handling

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Pages and Views
  - Admin Dashboard (page_admin_dashboard)
    - Responsive, single-column layout with stacked cards
    - KPI cards with bold numeric stats and growth indicators
    - Quick Actions panel with primary CTAs (suspend, refund, export, impersonate)
    - Search bar with advanced filters (name, email, userId, status)
    - Impersonation banner when active
  - Admin — User Management (page_admin_users)
    - Data grid/list with sortable columns (username, email, status, role, last active)
    - Search and multi-parameter filtering
    - Row actions: View Profile, Suspend/Unsuspend, Soft-Delete/Restore, Export
    - Bulk actions with checkboxes and bulk export/suspend
    - Profile drawer/modal with view/edit capabilities (restricted by role)
  - Admin — Content Moderation (page_admin_moderation)
    - Moderation queue with items: content snippet, reported reason, user, status
    - Actions: Remove content, Warn, Suspend, Mark as resolved, Undo
    - Challenges/Leaderboard disputes management with resolution workflows
    - Content operations panel for feature/pin/promote
  - Admin Auth & Impersonation UI
    - MFA prompts, IP allowlist status, login/logout flows
    - Impersonation session banner and warning
- Components and Interactions
  - RBAC-enabled UI controls (visible/hidden per role)
  - Confirm dialogs for destructive actions (suspend, delete, refund)
  - Undo toast/snackbar with action to revert recent admin actions
  - Audit trail viewer in admin sections
  - Data export progress indicators
- State Management
  - useState with arrays: initialize as useState<T[]>([]) for any list data
  - useEffect data fetching with guards: (data ?? []) and Array.isArray checks
  - Centralized hook for admin API interactions with error handling
- Accessibility
  - Keyboard navigable controls, aria-labels, proper focus management
  - High-contrast text and sufficient color contrast per UI tokens
- Performance
  - Debounced search, pagination, and lazy loading on large datasets
  - Efficient rendering with memoization for heavy list components
- Data Safety (Runtime Safety Rules)
  - Always use data ?? [] when consuming API results
  - Guard array operations: (items ?? []).map(...), Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
  - Validate API responses: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - Optional chaining for nested API payloads
  - Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

### Backend
- API Endpoints (examples; ensure strict RBAC)
  - POST /api/admin/login (admin authentication with MFA, IP allowlisting)
  - GET /api/admin/dashboard-metrics (RBAC: Admin)
  - GET /api/admin/users (RBAC: Admin, Auditor) with query params: q, status, role, page, pageSize
  - GET /api/admin/users/:id (RBAC: Admin, Auditor)
  - POST /api/admin/users/:id/suspend (RBAC: Admin) payload { reason, until?: Date }
  - POST /api/admin/users/:id/restore (RBAC: Admin)
  - POST /api/admin/users/:id/soft-delete (RBAC: Admin)
  - POST /api/admin/users/:id/restore-soft-delete (RBAC: Admin)
  - POST /api/admin/users/:id/export (RBAC: Admin) -> initiate export job
  - POST /api/admin/refund (RBAC: Admin) payload { userId, amount, reason }
  - GET /api/admin/audit-logs (RBAC: Auditor, Admin) with filters
  - GET /api/admin/moderation/queue (RBAC: Moderator, Admin)
  - POST /api/admin/moderation/actions (RBAC: Moderator, Admin) payload { itemId, action, notes }
  - POST /api/admin/content/feature (RBAC: Admin) payload { contentId, featureUntil }
  - POST /api/admin/impersonate (RBAC: Admin) payload { userId }
  - POST /api/admin/impersonation/stop (RBAC: Admin)
  - GET /api/admin/exports/:jobId/status (RBAC: Admin)
- Database Tables / Models
  - users: id, email, username, status (active/suspended/deleted), role (Admin/Moderator/Support/Auditor/User), impersonatingUserId, createdAt, updatedAt
  - audit_logs: id, adminUserId, action, targetType, targetId, detail, createdAt
  - refunds: id, userId, amount, reason, createdAt, status
  - moderation_reports: id, contentId, contentSnippet, reportedBy, reason, status, createdAt, resolvedAt
  - content_items: id, ownerId, content, status (active/removed/flagged), featuredUntil
  - impersonation_sessions: id, adminUserId, impersonatedUserId, startedAt, endedAt
  - exports: id, type, status, initiatedBy, createdAt, completedAt, fileUrl
  - soft_deletes: id, userId, deletedAt, restoredAt, reason
  - settings: id, ipAllowlist, mfaRequired, impersonationEnabled, auditLoggingEnabled
- Data Validation
  - Validate input payloads for presence, types, allowed values
  - Ensure referential integrity when linking to users or content
  - Rate limiting on admin endpoints
- Security
  - RBAC enforcement on all endpoints
  - MFA enforcement for admin login
  - IP allowlisting and session management
  - Audit trail persistence and tamper-proofing (immutable logs)
  - Content moderation actions reversible via audit logs and undo

### Integration
- Frontend-Backend communication
  - Use a centralized API client with consistent headers (Authorization, X-Admin-Context)
  - Include RBAC-aware guards in UI components to hide/disable actions not permitted
  - Use consistent error handling and user feedback (toast notifications, loading states)
- Data Flow
  - Admin Dashboard aggregates metrics from /dashboard-metrics
  - User Management fetches /users and renders list with pagination
  - Moderation uses /moderation/queue and /moderation/actions for workflow
  - Actions create audit logs via server-side handlers that populate audit_logs
  - Export flows create export jobs and provide status via /exports endpoints
- Concurrency and Consistency
  - Soft-delete and suspend are flag-based to preserve auditable state
  - Undo operations affect only allowed fields and create new audit entries
  - Impersonation sessions are logged and restricted to read/write permissions in a safe scope

## User Experience Flow
1. Admin authenticates with MFA and IP allowlisted access; sees Admin Dashboard with metrics and quick actions.
2. Admin navigates to User Management:
   - Uses search/filters to locate a user; views profile in a modal/drawer
   - Executes actions: suspend/restore, soft-delete/restore, export user data
   - Performs bulk actions on selected users; batch export queues an export job
3. Admin navigates to Content Moderation:
   - Reviews reports, selects action per item (remove content, warn, suspend user)
   - Uses content operations for featuring/pinning content and resolving disputes
   - Each action creates an audit log; undo option appears briefly after action
4. Admin navigates to Dashboard or impersonation:
   - Initiate impersonation for support, which renders a banner and restricts sensitive actions
   - After support session, stop impersonation and audit the session
5. All actions generate audit logs; admins can export audits, view history, and revert actions if allowed
6. All endpoints enforce RBAC; unauthorized attempts show proper guidance and are logged

## Technical Specifications

Data Models
- User
  - id, email, username, status (enum: active, suspended, deleted, pending), role (enum: Admin, Moderator, Support, Auditor, User), impersonatingUserId (nullable), createdAt, updatedAt
- AuditLog
  - id, adminUserId, action (string), targetType (string), targetId (string), detail (string), createdAt
- Refund
  - id, userId, amount, reason, status (enum: pending, completed, failed), createdAt, approvedBy
- ModerationReport
  - id, contentId, contentSnippet, reportedBy, reason, status (enum: open, in_review, resolved), createdAt, resolvedAt
- ContentItem
  - id, ownerId, content (string/blob), status (enum: active, removed, flagged), featuredUntil (nullable), createdAt, updatedAt
- ImpersonationSession
  - id, adminUserId, impersonatedUserId, startedAt, endedAt
- ExportJob
  - id, type (string), status (enum: pending, in_progress, completed, failed), initiatedBy, createdAt, completedAt, fileUrl
- SoftDeleteRecord
  - id, userId, deletedAt, restoredAt, reason
- Setting
  - id, ipAllowlist (array of strings), mfaRequired (boolean), impersonationEnabled (boolean), auditLoggingEnabled (boolean)

API Endpoints (methods, routes)
- POST /api/admin/auth/login
- GET /api/admin/dashboard-metrics
- GET /api/admin/users
- GET /api/admin/users/:id
- POST /api/admin/users/:id/suspend
- POST /api/admin/users/:id/restore
- POST /api/admin/users/:id/soft-delete
- POST /api/admin/users/:id/restore-soft-delete
- POST /api/admin/users/:id/export
- POST /api/admin/refund
- GET /api/admin/audit-logs
- GET /api/admin/moderation/queue
- POST /api/admin/moderation/actions
- POST /api/admin/content/feature
- POST /api/admin/impersonate
- POST /api/admin/impersonation/stop
- GET /api/admin/exports/:jobId/status

Security
- RBAC: enforce per-route access control
- MFA: required for admin login; fallback if MFA not configured
- IP allowlisting: deny except for permitted IPs
- Impersonation: banner, restricted actions, separate audit entries
- Data integrity: input validation, sanitized outputs, and tamper-evident audit logs
- Encryption: sensitive data at rest in DB; secure transport with TLS

Validation
- Validate all inputs with strict schemas
- Guard against null/undefined data before array operations
- Normalize API responses to arrays where applicable: const items = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []

Acceptance Criteria
- Admin authentication with MFA and IP allowlisting is enforced
- Admin roles: Admin, Moderator, Support, Auditor have appropriate access
- All admin actions are auditable with proper logs
- Soft-delete, suspend, and undo operations are available with safe rollback
- Impersonation mode is implemented with a clear banner and restricted scope
- Data export endpoints generate downloadable reports with correct formatting
- Frontend uses runtime-safe patterns for array handling (as per coding standards)
- UI components reflect RBAC permissions, with disabled/hidden actions for unauthorized roles
- All endpoints include input validation and error handling
- UI adheres to the design system (color tokens, typography, spacing, and responsive layout)

UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:
- Follow the visual style, color palette, typography, spacing, and layout rules described in the Visual Style section
- Use rounded cards, frosted-glass surfaces, warm gradients, and accent colors for primary actions
- Ensure consistency across Admin Dashboard, User Management, and Content Moderation pages
- Maintain accessible contrast, readable typography, and intuitive affordances
- Implement micro-interactions and feedback for admin actions (toasts, confetti on success, etc.)
- Ensure dark mode compatibility and accessible color treatments

Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety
CRITICAL: All generated code MUST guard against null/undefined values before calling array methods. Always use:
- Supabase results: data ?? []
- Array methods guarded: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
- useState for arrays: useState<Type[]>([])
- API responses: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- Optional chaining: obj?.property?.nested
- Destructuring defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

Project Context Alignment
- TARGET FEATURE: Admin Controls
- Associated Pages: page_admin_dashboard, page_admin_users, page_admin_moderation
- RBAC, soft-delete, suspend, impersonation, audit logs, and secure admin auth are core pillars
- The UI must be cohesive with QuestHabit's gamified yet calm design philosophy

Notes for AI Development Tool
- Implement robust unit tests for all frontend components and API endpoints
- Provide clear error messaging and retry logic
- Include feature flagging to enable/disable admin features in staging/production
- Document data contracts between frontend and backend, including expected response shapes and error formats
- Ensure all code paths handle potential null values safely per the runtime safety rules above

